      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by a second analyst not involved in original construction.",
      "rationale": "Each of the three modeling teams performed independent blind setup of the F1717 model from a common geometry and material specification document. Cross-team QoI comparisons showed agreement within 3%, confirming minimal analyst-driven use error. Formal peer review sign-off documented for each team. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics representation appropriate for quasi-static large-displacement bending with metal plasticity and frictional contact.",
      "rationale": "Continuum FEA with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity (Ti-6Al-4V, PEEK rod) and penalty-based frictional contact at screw-rod and connector interfaces. Geometric nonlinearity enabled. Model form validated against established literature for implant construct mechanics. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
