      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all primary QoIs.",
      "rationale": "For all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm), E/uval ranged from 0.31 to 1.44 across the 11 specimens and both laboratories. Maximum percent difference was 7.8%. All specimens satisfied both acceptance criteria simultaneously. Statistical summary tables provided in supporting documentation. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to regulatory submission metrics and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly relate to clinical construct stability and failure risk. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
